        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Fig. 2. Male diagnostic features of Pselaphodes aduncus sp. nov. A – antennal club; B – pronotum; C – metaventral process, in lateral view; D – protrochanter and profemur; E – apex of protibia; F – mesotrochanter and mesofemur; G – metatrochanter and metafemur; H – sternite IX; I–K – aedeagus, in dorsal (I), lateral (J), and ventral (K) view. Scale bar: 0.3 mm in A–B, D, F–G; 0.2 mm in C, I–K; 0.1 mm in E, H." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4488747/files/figure.png" .

